---
description: Enforce component-based architecture, prop-driven UI, and reusable design-system discipline across the project.
alwaysApply: true
---

- Core law: never build monolithic pages; build reusable components and assemble pages from them.
- Use feature-based architecture for new work; avoid layer-based organization for feature code.
- Keep presentational and container responsibilities separate.
- Pass content through typed props; avoid hard-coded copy inside reusable components.
- Use internal variants (`variant` props) instead of ad-hoc external style overrides.
- Use design tokens/CSS variables; avoid raw hard-coded style values.
- Extract repeated logic into focused composables; keep composables single-responsibility.
- Page files are assembly-only: no component internals, no page-level component logic/styles.

- 🚩 Duplicate markup that should be a reusable component.
- 🚩 Hard-coded style values instead of tokens.
- 🚩 Component logic implemented directly in page files.
- 🚩 Styling variants controlled externally instead of component API.
- 🚩 Hard-coded content inside components that should be props.
- 🚩 Primitive obsession for domain props (IDs/slugs/emails as unvalidated plain strings).
- 🚩 Data-fetching/side effects inside presentational components.
- 🚩 New feature code added in layer-based structure.

See `.cursor/skills/component-based-design-system/SKILL.md` for full patterns and examples.
